# Data Management

## Purpose

Data files in `src/data/` contain all site content. Edit these files to update the portfolio without touching component code.

## Data File Patterns

### Standard Export Pattern

```javascript
// Single named export for primary data
export const featuredProjects = [
  { /* item */ },
]

// Additional exports for related data
export const projectCategories = ['All', 'Full-Stack', 'Mobile App']
```

## Data Structures

### Projects (`projects.js`)

```javascript
export const featuredProjects = [
  {
    id: 1,                           // Unique identifier (number)
    title: 'Project Name',           // Display title
    shortDescription: 'Brief...',    // 1-2 sentences for cards
    longDescription: `Multi-line     // Full description for modal
      description with markdown-like 
      formatting allowed.`,
    technologies: [                  // Array of tech strings
      'React', 'Flask', 'MySQL'
    ],
    category: 'Full-Stack',          // Must match projectCategories
    features: [                      // Key features list
      'Feature one',
      'Feature two'
    ],
    performanceMetrics: {
      loadTime: '< 2s',              // String with unit
      bundleSize: '245KB',           // String with unit
      lighthouseScore: 92            // Number 0-100 or null
