## Guidelines

### ✅ DO

```javascript
// Use consistent structure
{ id: 1, title: 'First' },
{ id: 2, title: 'Second' },

// Use descriptive, SEO-friendly text
shortDescription: 'Production geolocation API with credit-based billing'

// Keep technology names consistent
technologies: ['React', 'Flask']  // Not 'ReactJS', 'flask'

// Use null for optional missing values
liveDemoUrl: null  // Not undefined or empty string

// Order items by importance/recency
// Most recent/featured items first
```

### ❌ DON'T

```javascript
// DON'T: Inconsistent IDs
{ id: 'proj-1' },  // Use numbers for IDs
{ id: 2 },

// DON'T: HTML in descriptions
longDescription: '<strong>Bold</strong>'  // Plain text only

// DON'T: Broken URLs
liveDemoUrl: 'example.com'  // Need full https://

// DON'T: Undefined for missing optional
liveDemoUrl: undefined  // Use null

// DON'T: Empty arrays when no data
features: []  // Either have content or remove property
```

## Adding New Content

### New Project

1. Add object to `featuredProjects` array in `projects.js`
2. Ensure unique `id` (increment from highest existing)
3. Category must exist in `projectCategories`
4. Technologies should be consistent with existing names

### New Skill Category

1. Add object to `skillCategories` array in `skills.js`
2. `icon` must be valid Lucide icon name
3. Each skill needs `name`, `level` (0-100), `description`

### New Career Position

1. Add object to `careerPositions` array in `career.js`
2. Set `isCurrent: true` for current position
3. Update previous current position to `isCurrent: false`

## Icon Name Reference (for skills)

Valid icon names from Lucide:
- `Code` - Frontend/general coding
- `Server` - Backend
- `Smartphone` - Mobile
- `Globe` - Cloud/DevOps
- `Database` - Data
- `Palette` - Design
- `Terminal` - CLI/Scripts

